---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import onlineEnrolImage from "../../../images/future-state/online-enrol.png";
import ppt004Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.004.png";
import ppt005Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.005.png";
import ppt006Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.006.png";
import ppt008Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.008.png";
import ppt009Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.009.png";
import ppt011Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.011.png";
import ppt013Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.013.png";
import ppt015Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.015.png";
import ppt018Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.018.png";
import ppt021Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.021.png";
import ppt026Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.026.png";
import ppt029Image from "../../../images/future-state/ppt/XpressWeigh-vision.029.png";
---

<BaseLayout title="Future State · Case Study">
  <section>
    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/home">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span aria-current="page">Future State</span>
    </nav>

    <h1 class="hero-title">
      Future State journey mapping as a tool to make <span
        class="flourish-period">.</span
      >
    </h1>

    <ul class="meta-list meta-list--casestudy meta-list--pills">
      <li></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="hero-wrapper">
      <section class="hero-lead">
        <p>
          <strong>
            As Slimming World embarked on full digital transformaion, I used
            journey maps to shape the conversations aroudn what the future state
            should be.
          </strong>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="card card--role card--compact card--transparent">
        <h2>Role</h2>
        <ul class="role-list"></ul>
      </section>
    </div>

    <ul class="tools-list"></ul>
    <h1 class="phase-title"><span>Previously</span></h1>

    <p>
      Around 18 months before transformation was formally announced, I presented
      a service-led ecosystem vision outlining how more connected systems could
      reshape interactions across the model.
    </p>
    <div class="image-row image-row--full image-row--6">
      <Image src={ppt004Image} alt="Future state vision slide 1" />
      <Image src={ppt005Image} alt="Future state vision slide 2" />
      <Image src={ppt006Image} alt="Future state vision slide 3" />
      <Image src={ppt008Image} alt="Future state vision slide 4" />
      <Image src={ppt009Image} alt="Future state vision slide 5" />
      <Image src={ppt011Image} alt="Future state vision slide 6" />
    </div>
    <div class="image-row image-row--full image-row--6">
      <Image src={ppt013Image} alt="Future state vision slide 7" />
      <Image src={ppt015Image} alt="Future state vision slide 8" />
      <Image src={ppt018Image} alt="Future state vision slide 9" />
      <Image src={ppt021Image} alt="Future state vision slide 10" />
      <Image src={ppt026Image} alt="Future state vision slide 11" />
      <Image src={ppt029Image} alt="Future state vision slide 12" />
    </div>
    <p class="image-row--caption">
      Long before transformation began, I had mapped and presented one vision of
      the future to then then MD. A few sample slides shown.
    </p>

    <section class="card content-block">
      <h2>Problem</h2>

      <p>
        When transformation was formally announced, there was broad agreement
        that systems needed to become more connected, but little clarity on what
        that meant in practice. Proposals such as digital membership cards,
        online enrolment and online payments made sense individually, and there
        was a clear push toward greater member self-service. However, the
        service consequences weren’t being modelled end to end. Without a shared
        view of how these changes would affect member–consultant interaction —
        particularly in a model built on human connection — there was a risk of
        solving isolated problems while shifting complexity elsewhere.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="card content-block">
      <h2>Modelling sign-up as a connected system</h2>

      <p>I began with online enrolment as a standalone map.</p>

      <p>
        Moving enrolment online appears straightforward, but in this model it
        fundamentally alters how and when the relationship between member and
        consultant begins. I mapped the end-to-end flow from initial intent
        through to first in-group interaction, modelling how data, ownership and
        visibility would transfer across systems.
      </p>

      <p>
        Online enrolment also exposed a structural tension within the franchise
        model.
      </p>

      <p>
        When a member signs up to a Consultant’s group through the company
        website, who owns that relationship and its data? The central
        organisation facilitates enrolment, but the ongoing service is delivered
        by the Consultant.
      </p>

      <p>
        The map did not resolve these questions, but it brought them to the
        surface. By modelling the flow end to end, it made visible where
        responsibility, visibility and control were ambiguous. This created a
        clearer foundation for subsequent discussion, particularly as digital
        enrolment, membership cards and payments were explored in more detail.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="image-row image-row--full-bleed">
      <p class="image-overlay">Tap to view full map</p>
      <button
        class="lightbox-trigger"
        type="button"
        data-lightbox-target="online-enrol-map"
        aria-label="Open online enrolment map full size"
      >
        <Image
          src={onlineEnrolImage}
          alt="Online enrolment journey map"
          widths={[480, 768, 1024, 1440, 1920]}
          sizes="200vw"
        />
      </button>
    </section>
    <dialog
      class="lightbox"
      data-lightbox="online-enrol-map"
      aria-label="Online enrolment map"
    >
      <div class="lightbox__actions">
        <button class="lightbox__toggle" type="button" aria-pressed="false">
          Fit height
        </button>
        <button class="lightbox__close" type="button" aria-label="Close">
          ×
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="lightbox__inner">
        <div class="lightbox__image">
          <img
            src={onlineEnrolImage.src}
            alt="Online enrolment journey map"
            draggable="false"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </dialog>
    <p class="image-row--caption">
      Online enrolment map used to model the end-to-end member sign-up journey.
    </p>

    <section class="card content-block">
      <h2>Build</h2>
    </section>

    <section class="card content-block">
      <h2>Testing</h2>
    </section>

    <section class="card content-block">
      <h2>Impact</h2>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
<script type="module" src="/scripts/lightbox.js"></script>
